Author:  DAWSON
Vol / Page:  123
Edition:
Quote:  More brilliant splashes of colour ... may be provided by certain mistletoes which commonly parasite the beeches. <i>Peraxilla colensoi</i>, usually found on silver beech, and <i>P. tetrapetala</i> have bright red flowers. <i>Alepis flavida</i> with orange-yellow to yellow flowers used to be common, but has now been depleted by opossums.
